text: Stanislaus County ( or ) is a county in the Central Valley of the U.S. state of California. As of the 2020 census, the population was 552,878. The county seat is Modesto. Stanislaus County was founded in 1854. == Communities == === Cities === * Ceres * Hughson * Modesto * Newman * Oakdale * Patterson * Riverbank * Turlock * Waterford == References == Category:1854 establishments in California
title: Stanislaus County, California
